F.     Planned Changes to Improve Safety



Chlorine System



In September 1994, the chlorine system was thoroughly examined for safety hazards by way of a Process Hazard Analysis (PHA).  In addition, PHA Revalidations were conducted in March 1999, June 2004, February 2009, and January 2014.  The January 2014 PHA Revalidation consisted of:



?    A review of the PHA Requirements / History (Overview / Training Session);

?    A detailed review of the recommended action items from 2009 PHA Revalidation Study; 

?    An equipment list review;

?    A detailed review of any changes to the chlorine system since the 2009 study (reviewed Management of Change Records);

?    A discussion of any releases of chlorine since the 2009 study (review of Incident Investigation Records);

?    Development of HAZOP log sheets;

?    Completion of Emergency Response, Chlorine Checklist, Chlorine What-If Questions, and External Events checklists; and

?    A facility inspection.



The mitigation measures included enhanced emergency response and operating procedures.  All recommendations resulting from the revalidation study are due to be completed by January 2015.



